result.execSummary:
The defendant Dante T Nash was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Fine to be paid $50.00 a month commencing 11/01/2022 and each month thereafter or penalty of civil judgment for non-payment.

9:27 AM Defendant Dante T Nash in court.  Attorney Paul Garland Bonneson in court for Dante T Nash. District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin by Abigail Kincheloe. Victim rights have been complied with by the Waukesha County District Attorneys Office.  

Prosecuting attorney moves to amend to Disorderly Conduct contrary to section 13.102(c)(8)  of the Waukesha County Code of Ordinances, with agreement from Defendant to forfeit gun.  Court approves amendment.  No contest plea entered.  Court finds the defendant guilty.

Court orders the following:

$267.50 to be paid at $50/month, commencing on 11/01/2022, and the first of every month until paid in full, civil judgment entered subject to collections, as penalty for non payment of fine. 
Court orders forfeiture of firearm.

Defense has received an offer and discovery and requests another date to speak to charging DA. Court sets.
